UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0022199683800038
AB  - This paper investigates the behavior of exchange rates under the floating rate system when the trade balance responds to the exchange rate in a J-curve fashion; and when exchange rate expectations are rational, but speculators are risk averse. The major findings are (I) that speculators will stabilize the floating exchange rate system, provided capital mobility is sufficiently high; (2) unless the degree of capital mobility exceeds an even higher critical level, exchange rates will oscillate around their long-run equilibrium values; and (3) a real unanticipated disturbance will cause the exchange rate to overshoot its long-run equilibrium level.
