AB  - Using the standard trade model with three countries, and allowing for substitutability in both production and consumption, this paper demonstrates that a country may gain by giving a transfer, that the receiver may lose, and that these two phenomena may appear at the same time. This result is an extension of Gale's example in a fixed-coefficient model, where he shows both transferer and transferee may become better off harming the third country; and it is contrasted with the traditional welfare proposition whereby a giver is immiserized and a recipient is enriched.
